## Limitations

The analysis is limited by the availability of sources and the potential bias in opinion-based articles. The discussion is primarily centered on the United States, which may not fully represent the global perspective on the separation of church and state. Additionally, the complexity of the topic means that not all nuances and historical contexts can be fully explored in a brief report. Further research could include more diverse international perspectives and a deeper legal analysis of court cases related to this issue.